annotations.title: NASA's Perseverance rover lands on Mars successfully - Event Date: February 18th, 2021
Touchdown! NASA's Mars Perseverance Rover Safely Lands on Red Planet - NASA
NASAs Ingenuity Mars Helicopter Succeeds in Historic First Flight - NASA

content.text:
- **Feb. 18, 2021**  NASAs Perseverance rover successfully landed in Mars Jezero Crater, kicking off a mission to search for ancient microbial life and collect the first Martian rock samples for future return to Earth ([isitaholidaytoday.com](https://isitaholidaytoday.com/events/perseverance-mars-rover-designed-explore#:~:text=The%20NASA%20Mars%202020%20mission,Image)) ([www.nasa.gov](https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/touchdown-nasas-mars-perseverance-rover-safely-lands-on-red-planet/#:~:text=rover%20will%20investigate%20the%20rock,send%20to%20the%20Red%20Planet)).  
- **Apr. 19, 2021**  NASAs Ingenuity Mars Helicopter carried out the first powered, controlled flight on another planet (Mars), demonstrating a groundbreaking new capability for aerial exploration on the Red Planet ([www.nasa.gov](https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasas-ingenuity-mars-helicopter-succeeds-in-historic-first-flight/#:~:text=In%20this%20video%20captured%20by,Caltech%2FASU%2FMSSS)).
